  "abstract": "ICGV-SM 85048 (Reg. no. GP-90, PI 598134), an improved\r\nSpanish peanut (Arachis hypogaea L. subsp.fastigiata var. vitlgaris)\r\ngermplasm, was developed at the SADC/ICRISAT (Southern African\r\nDevelopment Community/International Crops Research Institute\r\nfor the Semi-Arid Tropics) Groundnut Project in Malawi. It\r\nwas first tested at the Mauritius Sugar Industry Research Institute\r\n(MSIRI), Mauritius, in 1988. After evaluations in on-station and\r\non-farm trials, it was released in 1992 as 'Stella' in Mauritius (8).\r\nIt is suitable for cultivation both in sugarcane (Sacchanim officinarum\r\nL.) interrows and in pure stands",
